{"title_page": "Tau Films", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name               =  Tau Films\n| logo               = \n| type               = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| key_people         = \n| industry           =  [[Visual effects]], [[Computer animation]]\n| products           = \n| services =  [[Visual effects]], [[Computer animation]]\n| owner              = \n| num_employees      = \n| homepage           =  [http://www.taufilms.com/taufilms taufilms.com]\n| foundation         = [[2014 in film|{{Start date and age|2014}}]]\n| founders           = John Hughes, Mandeep Singh, and Walt Jones \n| location           = [[United States]], [[Malaysia]], [[India]], [[China]], [[Canada]].<ref name=about>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.taufilms.com/taufilms/pages/about-us/\n|title=Welcome to Tau Films\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=Tau Films Official Website: About Us\n}}</ref> \n}}\n\n'''Tau Films''' is an American [[visual effects]] and [[animation]] company with locations in the [[United States]], [[Malaysia]], [[India]], [[China]], and [[Canada]].\n==History==\nTau Films was founded in 2014 by John Hughes,<ref name=jh>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1220128/?ref_=tt_rv\n|title=John Hughes\n|accessdate=2019-04-04\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[IMDb]]\n}}</ref> Mandeep Singh,<ref name=ms>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2515683/\n|title=Mandeep Singh\n|accessdate=2019-04-04\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[IMDb]]\n}}</ref> and Walt Jones.<ref name=about/><ref name=wj>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1639892/\n|title=Walt Jones\n|accessdate=2019-04-04\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[IMDb]]\n}}</ref> In 2015, it was nominated for ''Outstanding Visual Effects in a Special Venue Project'' at the [[13th Visual Effects Society Awards#Other categories|13th Visual Effects Society Awards]] for its work on the [[Amusement_park#Rides_and_attractions|amusement park]] special venue-ride film ''[[Movie Park Germany#The Hollywood Street Set|The Lost Temple (Movie Park Germany)]]''.<ref name=mpg>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.inparkmagazine.com/deep-inside-the-lost-temple-movie-park-germany-delivers-media-based-thrills/\n|title=Deep inside the Lost Temple: Movie Park Germany delivers media-based thrills\n|accessdate=2019-03-22\n|last=Palicki\n|first=Martin\n|date=2014-08-27\n|publisher=InPark Magazine\n}}</ref><ref name=ves13/> It has since produced other special venue-ride films such as ''The Forbidden Caves ([[Bobbejaanland]])''<ref name=fc>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.inparkmagazine.com/three-holovis-projects-issue-58/\n|title=Three Holovis Projects: The Forbidden Caves\n|accessdate=2019-03-22\n|last=Kleiman\n|first=Joe\n|date=2015-08-28\n|publisher=InPark Magazine\n}}</ref> and ''[[PortAventura World#Amusement rides using motion pictures|Racing Legends at Ferrari Land (PortAventura World:Ferrari Land]])''.<ref name=inparkfl>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.inparkmagazine.com/mousetrappe-ferrari-land/\n|title=Mousetrappe Announces New Port Aventura Ferrari Land Attractions and New Staff\n|accessdate=2019-03-14\n|last=Kleiman\n|first=Joe\n|date=2017-04-21\n|publisher=InPark Magazine\n}}</ref> It also created ''Delusion: Lies Within'' ([[virtual reality]] [[episodic storytelling]]).<ref name=delusion>{{cite web\n|url=https://samsungvr.com/portal/whatsnew/whats_new_181224\n|title=From Stage To VR : Enter \u2018Delusion: Lies Within\u2019\n|accessdate=2019-03-17\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[Samsung Electronics]]\n}}</ref> Tau has worked on films such as ''Evil Nature'' (2015),<ref name=en>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/98597/explore-the-evil-nature-of-this-proof-of-concept-trailer/\n|title=Explore the Evil Nature of this Proof of Concept Trailer\n|accessdate=2019-03-23\n|last=Moore\n|first=Debi\n|date=2015-04-27\n|publisher=[[Dread Central]]\n}}</ref> ''[[Baahubali: The Beginning]]'' (2015),<ref name=frets>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2015/07/19/bollywood-frets-as-baahubali-sets-new-box-office-records/#2a5578eb33c7\n|title=Bollywood Frets As 'Baahubali' Sets New Box Office Records\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Cain\n|first=Rob\n|date=2015-07-19\n|publisher=[[Forbes]]\n}}</ref><ref name=know>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/baahubali-5-things-indian-blockbuster-808778\n|title='Baahubali': 5 Things to Know About India's Record-Breaking Blockbuster\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Bhushan\n|first=Nyay\n|date=2015-07-15\n|publisher=[[Hollywood Reporter]]\n}}</ref><ref name=targets>{{cite web\n|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/india-saga-baahubali-targets-the-world-with-ramoji-film-city-1201490313/\n|title=India Saga \u2018Baahubali\u2019 Targets the World With Ramoji Film City\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Ramachandran\n|first=Naman \n|date=2015-05-08\n|publisher=Variety\n}}</ref><ref name=bison>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/watch-how-malaysia-s-tau-films-created-baahubali-s-bull-scene/story-BpCE9RDtwdobkN4tRw465O.html\n|title=Watch: How Malaysia\u2019s Tau Films created Baahubali\u2019s bull scene\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2016-01-08\n|publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]\n}}</ref><ref name=express>{{cite web\n|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/hollywood-quality-on-limited-budget-will-be-achievement-ss-rajamouli/\n|title=Hollywood quality on limited budget will be achievement: SS Rajamouli\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2015-06-07\n|publisher=[[The Indian Express]]\n}}</ref> ''[[2.0\u00a0(film)|2.0]]'' (2018),<ref name=national>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.thenational.ae/arts-culture/film/vfx-expert-from-hollywood-calls-rajnikanth-s-2-0-most-challenging-project-1.796912\n|title=VFX expert from Hollywood calls Rajnikanth's 2.0 'most challenging' project\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Shyam\n|first=Kumar \n|date=2018-03-07\n|publisher=The National\n}}</ref><ref name=making>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/the-making-of-2-0-vfx-featurette-see-the-hard-work-put-into-rajinikanth-akshay-kumar-s-film/story-CYeIXO1qApcL1xNAyNX5DN.html\n|title=The making of 2.0 VFX featurette: See the hard work put into Rajinikanth-Akshay Kumar\u2019s film\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Sundar\n|first=Priyanka\n|date=2018-03-07\n|publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]\n}}</ref> ''[[Crazy Alien]]'' (2019),<ref name=adi>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tUjPZqQt3lQ\n|title=AU2019: Making of \"Crazy Alien\"\n|accessdate=2019-09-27\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2019-10-29\n|publisher=[[Autodesk]] India\n}}</ref><ref name=event>{{cite web\n|url=https://nat24.com/impact/asias-largest-event-in-gaming-animation-visual-effects-inaugurated/\n|title=Asia\u2019s Largest Event in Gaming, Animation, Visual Effects inaugurated\n|accessdate=2019-09-26\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2019-06-24\n|publisher=Nat24\n}}</ref> the 2019 [[Nicolas Cage]] film ''[[Primal (2019 film)|Primal]]'',<ref name=stalk>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.animationmagazine.net/vfx/killer-cg-creatures-stalk-nic-cage-in-primal-with-help-from-ziva-vfx/\n|title=Killer CG Creatures Stalk Nic Cage in \u2018Primal\u2019 with Help from Ziva VFX\n|accessdate=2019-11-27\n|last=Milligan\n|first=Mercedes\n|date=2019-11-26\n|publisher=[[Animation Magazine]]\n}}</ref><ref name=screenan>{{cite web\n|url=https://screenanarchy.com/2019/11/interview-primal-director-nick-powell-on-his-old-school-action-adventure-thriller.html\n|title=Interview: PRIMAL Director Nick Powell On His Old-School Action-Adventure Thriller\n|accessdate=2019-11-13\n|last=Garcia\n|first=Eric\n|date=2019-11-11\n|publisher=[[Screen Anarchy]]\n}}</ref> and ''[[Skyfire (film)|Skyfire]]'' (2019), directed by [[Simon West]].<ref name=var0514>{{cite web\n|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/cannes-skyfire-simon-west-meridian-base-fx-1203214530/\n|title=Cannes: \u2018Skyfire,\u2019 China\u2019s First Big-Budget Disaster Movie, Shopped by Meridian Ent. (EXCLUSIVE)\n|accessdate=2019-05-14\n|last=Davis\n|first=Rebecca\n|date=2019-05-14\n|publisher= [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]\n}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n;2019\n*''[[Skyfire (film)|Skyfire]]''\n*''[[Primal (2019 film)|Primal]]''\n* ''[[Crazy Alien]]''\n\n;2018\n* ''[[2.0\u00a0(film)|2.0]]''\n* ''Delusion: Lies Within''\n\n;2017\n* ''[[WildAid]]: [[Jackie Chan]] & [[Pangolin]]s (Kung Fu Pangolin)''<ref name=pangolins>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/world/2017-08/23/content_31006476.htm\n|title=Jackie Chan fights for pangolins\n|accessdate=2019-03-17\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2017-08-23\n|publisher=[[China Daily]]\n}}</ref> \n* ''[[PortAventura World#Amusement rides using motion pictures|Racing Legends at Ferrari Land'' (PortAventura World:Ferrari Land]]) \n\n;2015\n*''Evil Nature''\n* ''[[Baahubali: The Beginning]]''\n*''[[Everest (2015 film)|Everest]]''\n*''[[Warner Bros. Studio Tour London \u2013 The Making of Harry Potter#Platform 9\u00be|Hogwarts Express - London'' (Warner Bros. Studio Tour London- Platform 9\u00be]])\n* '' The Forbidden Caves'' ([[Bobbejaanland]])\n\n;2014\n* ''[[Movie Park Germany#The Hollywood Street Set|The Lost Temple'' (Movie Park Germany)]]\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n*'''2015''': '''Nominated -''' ''Outstanding Visual Effects in a Special Venue Project'', [[13th Visual Effects Society Awards#Other categories|13th Visual Effects Society Awards]]. ''The Lost Temple'' ([[Movie Park Germany]])<ref name=ves13>{{cite web\n|url=https://visualeffectssociety.com/portfolio-items/2014-13th-annual-ves-awards/?portfolioCats=29\n|title=13TH ANNUAL VES AWARDS\n|accessdate=2019-03-22\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2015-02-04\n|publisher=[[Visual Effects Society]]\n}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|www.taufilms.com/taufilms}}\n*{{IMDb company|id=0549099|company=Tau Films}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Companies|United States|Los Angeles|California|Film|Animation}}\n{{Animation industry in the United States}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tau Films}}\n[[Category:Computer animation]]\n[[Category:Visual effects companies]]\n[[Category:American animation studios]]\n[[Category:Entertainment companies based in California]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name               =  Tau Films\n| logo               = \n| type               = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| key_people         = \n| industry           =  [[Visual effects]], [[Computer animation]]\n| products           = \n| services =  [[Visual effects]], [[Computer animation]]\n| owner              = \n| num_employees      = \n| homepage           =  [http://www.taufilms.com/taufilms taufilms.com]\n| foundation         = [[2014 in film|{{Start date and age|2014}}]]\n| founders           = John Hughes, Mandeep Singh, and Walt Jones \n| location           = [[United States]], [[Malaysia]], [[India]], [[China]], [[Canada]].<ref name=about>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.taufilms.com/taufilms/pages/about-us/\n|title=Welcome to Tau Films\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=Tau Films Official Website: About Us\n}}</ref> \n}}\n\n'''Tau Films''' is an American [[visual effects]] and [[animation]] company with locations in the [[United States]], [[Malaysia]], [[India]], [[China]], and [[Canada]].\n==History==\nTau Films was founded in 2014 by John Hughes,<ref name=jh>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1220128/?ref_=tt_rv\n|title=John Hughes\n|accessdate=2019-04-04\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[IMDb]]\n}}</ref> Mandeep Singh,<ref name=ms>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2515683/\n|title=Mandeep Singh\n|accessdate=2019-04-04\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[IMDb]]\n}}</ref> and Walt Jones.<ref name=about/><ref name=wj>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1639892/\n|title=Walt Jones\n|accessdate=2019-04-04\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[IMDb]]\n}}</ref> In 2015, it was nominated for ''Outstanding Visual Effects in a Special Venue Project'' at the [[13th Visual Effects Society Awards#Other categories|13th Visual Effects Society Awards]] for its work on the [[Amusement_park#Rides_and_attractions|amusement park]] special venue-ride film ''[[Movie Park Germany#The Hollywood Street Set|The Lost Temple (Movie Park Germany)]]''.<ref name=mpg>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.inparkmagazine.com/deep-inside-the-lost-temple-movie-park-germany-delivers-media-based-thrills/\n|title=Deep inside the Lost Temple: Movie Park Germany delivers media-based thrills\n|accessdate=2019-03-22\n|last=Palicki\n|first=Martin\n|date=2014-08-27\n|publisher=InPark Magazine\n}}</ref><ref name=ves13/> It has since produced other special venue-ride films such as ''The Forbidden Caves ([[Bobbejaanland]])''<ref name=fc>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.inparkmagazine.com/three-holovis-projects-issue-58/\n|title=Three Holovis Projects: The Forbidden Caves\n|accessdate=2019-03-22\n|last=Kleiman\n|first=Joe\n|date=2015-08-28\n|publisher=InPark Magazine\n}}</ref> and ''[[PortAventura World#Amusement rides using motion pictures|Racing Legends at Ferrari Land (PortAventura World:Ferrari Land]])''.<ref name=inparkfl>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.inparkmagazine.com/mousetrappe-ferrari-land/\n|title=Mousetrappe Announces New Port Aventura Ferrari Land Attractions and New Staff\n|accessdate=2019-03-14\n|last=Kleiman\n|first=Joe\n|date=2017-04-21\n|publisher=InPark Magazine\n}}</ref> It also created ''Delusion: Lies Within'' ([[virtual reality]] [[episodic storytelling]]).<ref name=delusion>{{cite web\n|url=https://samsungvr.com/portal/whatsnew/whats_new_181224\n|title=From Stage To VR : Enter \u2018Delusion: Lies Within\u2019\n|accessdate=2019-03-17\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=\n|publisher=[[Samsung Electronics]]\n}}</ref> Tau has worked on films such as ''Evil Nature'' (2015),<ref name=en>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/98597/explore-the-evil-nature-of-this-proof-of-concept-trailer/\n|title=Explore the Evil Nature of this Proof of Concept Trailer\n|accessdate=2019-03-23\n|last=Moore\n|first=Debi\n|date=2015-04-27\n|publisher=[[Dread Central]]\n}}</ref> ''[[Baahubali: The Beginning]]'' (2015),<ref name=frets>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2015/07/19/bollywood-frets-as-baahubali-sets-new-box-office-records/#2a5578eb33c7\n|title=Bollywood Frets As 'Baahubali' Sets New Box Office Records\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Cain\n|first=Rob\n|date=2015-07-19\n|publisher=[[Forbes]]\n}}</ref><ref name=know>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/baahubali-5-things-indian-blockbuster-808778\n|title='Baahubali': 5 Things to Know About India's Record-Breaking Blockbuster\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Bhushan\n|first=Nyay\n|date=2015-07-15\n|publisher=[[Hollywood Reporter]]\n}}</ref><ref name=targets>{{cite web\n|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/india-saga-baahubali-targets-the-world-with-ramoji-film-city-1201490313/\n|title=India Saga \u2018Baahubali\u2019 Targets the World With Ramoji Film City\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=Ramachandran\n|first=\u00a0Naman \n|date=2015-05-08\n|publisher=[[Variety\u00a0(magazine)|Variety]]\n}}</ref><ref name=bison>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/watch-how-malaysia-s-tau-films-created-baahubali-s-bull-scene/story-BpCE9RDtwdobkN4tRw465O.html\n|title=Watch: How Malaysia\u2019s Tau Films created Baahubali\u2019s bull scene\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2016-01-08\n|publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]\n}}</ref><ref name=express>{{cite web\n|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/hollywood-quality-on-limited-budget-will-be-achievement-ss-rajamouli/\n|title=Hollywood quality on limited budget will be achievement: SS Rajamouli\n|accessdate=2019-03-13\n|last=\n|first=\n|date=2015-06-07\n|publisher=[[The Indian Express]]\n}}</ref> ''[[2.0\u00a0(film)|2.0]]'' (2018),<ref name=national>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.thenational.ae/arts-culture/film/vfx-expert-fro